Source: Omranarch.comThe development has been described as the largest smart city in the Middle East. The UAE's Mars Mission (Hope Probe) and Saudi Arabia's NEOM were also awarded during the conference. The new administrative capital comprises the central business district, including 19 hotel, residential and administrative towers beside the Iconic Tower, as well as schools, restaurants, and a hospital. The capital also has a governmental district that encompasses the Cabinet's building, 34 other buildings and different ministries.Article originally published on World Architecture Community.